{
  "texts": [
    "However, the reverse was also found true.",
    "With NLI, interactions did not seem \"natural\" to explain in language for complex tasks, such as visualizing BAM tracks.",
    "Furthermore, there was skepticism towards NLI due to the potential lack of accuracy in interpreting the authoring intent-then needing to revisit those authoring actions-and concerns about privacy and data handling.",
    "Communicating Visually for Visualizations.",
    "Participants were most unfamiliar with VbD and example-based techniques."
  ]
}